From Oliver Jones Subject Re X Design choice for color handling question In article Joseph Sirosh writes did X designers decide to not associate the color with the object being drawn and instead associate it with the display it is being drawn on In the drawing attributes were bundled into drawing requests that is the server's drawing model was This caused problems with performance and network traffic so the redesign included the graphic context to codify the drawing Most application designers who want to draw things in several different colors create a GC for each color during initialization then pass the GC id in each drawing For more information see Scheifler and Gettys's article in the ACM Transactions on